description:
&lt;p&gt;Band 6 Occupational Therapist - Trauma and Orthopaedics. Fixed Term Contract For 6 months. Full Time hours and Part Time hours are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, skilled and experienced, Specialist Occupational Therapist to join our Trauma and Orthopaedic Team at the Royal Cornwall Hospitals Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post requires the specialist assessment, treatment, and goal setting of a mixed caseload of acute adult inpatients from the trauma wards. You will have the opportunity to manage an acute caseload with a high turnover of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a team member who can provide decisive and effective Occupational Therapy input, and who has the confidence and energy to work in this field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have effective communication skills and a flexible and dynamic approach to your work as an Occupational Therapist? Do you have good leadership qualities and an ability to work calmly under pressure, both as part of a team and independently? Can you demonstrate up to date clinical knowledge and training in trauma and orthopaedics? If so, we would love you to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job share considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trauma OT Clinical Lead - Tina Pascoe on Tel: 01872 250000, bleep 3816.&lt;/p&gt;
